---
description: "Core stack and conventions"
alwaysApply: true
---
Stack: Python 3.12, FastAPI (async), React 18 / Vite / TypeScript, LiteLLM, Ollama (Docker), Qdrant (Docker).

All I/O-performing functions must be async. Sync helpers are allowed for pure computation only.

All model names, provider URLs, and tool names come from settings.json or litellm_config.yaml — resolved at runtime, never hardcoded in application logic.

Streaming via SSE is the primary response path. ChatOrchestrator.handle_message() returns AsyncIterator[str].

Use dataclasses for data transfer objects. Use Pydantic for config/settings validation only.

Naming: snake_case for Python, camelCase for TypeScript. Files: lowercase with underscores (Python), PascalCase components (TSX).